recent_25_results.question: 1.1 What is the role of a prototype program in problem solving?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 1.1 The role of a prototype program is to help spot key problems that may arise during the actual programing.

recent_25_results.question: 1.1 What is the role of a prototype program in problem solving?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 1.1 the prototype program gives a general idea of what the end product will do, without the time and effort to write out the entire program.

recent_25_results.question: 1.1 What is the role of a prototype program in problem solving?

recent_25_results.question: 1.1 What is the role of a prototype program in problem solving?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 1.1 Prototype programming is an approach to programming that enables one to take an organized approach to developing an effective program with minimal errors and a strategic pattern when solving a problem. i.e. book gave an example of a costumer withdrawing money from a bank, the approach that was taking on a pseudo code level during the OOA/Design lvl before proceeding into creating a solution.

recent_25_results.question: 1.2 What stages in the software life cycle are influenced by the testing stage?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 1.2 Refining and possibly the design if the testing phase reveals problems in the design. Production can be affected if the program is unworkable in its current form which will lead to a later production time than originally estimated. Also affects coding because after testing you may need to rewrite the code for the program to remove errors.

recent_25_results.question: 1.2 What stages in the software life cycle are influenced by the testing stage?
